'''Antonio Rüdiger''' ({{IPA|de|anˈtoːni̯o ˈʁyːdiɡɐ|-|De-Rüdiger.ogg}}; born 3 March 1993) is a German professional footballer who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{Spanish football updater|Real Madrid}} club [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]]. He is known for his aggressive playing style, speed, tackling ability and strong aerial presence.<ref name="BestCentreBacks">{{cite web |date=27 March 2023 |title=Ranked! The 10 best centre-backs in the world |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/best-centre-backs-defenders-in-the-world |access-date=10 May 2023 |website=FourFourTwo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Best defenders in the world 2023 |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/tv/sport/football/best-defenders-world/ |access-date=23 May 2023 |website=Radio Times |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=8 May 2022 |title=Van Dijk, Dias, Rudiger: Who is the best centre-back in the world? |url=https://www.givemesport.com/88005245-van-dijk-dias-rudiger-who-is-the-best-centre-back-in-the-world/ |access-date=23 May 2023 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Altimas |first=Callum |date=9 October 2023 |title=Ranking the 15 best defenders in world football right now |url=https://www.givemesport.com/best-defenders-world-football-ranked/ |access-date= |website=GiveMeSport}}</ref>

Rüdiger began his career at [[VfB Stuttgart]], representing [[VfB Stuttgart II|their reserves]] in [[3. Liga]] and the first team in the [[Bundesliga]]. In 2015 he joined [[AS Roma|Roma]], initially on loan and a year later for a €9&nbsp;million fee. He was signed by [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in 2017 for an estimated £27&nbsp;million, where he won the [[FA Cup]] in his first season, followed by the [[UEFA Europa League]] in his second season, and the [[UEFA Champions League]] in 2021. In 2022, he was signed by Real Madrid, winning a [[Copa del Rey]] in his first season, as well as La Liga and a second Champions League title in 2024.

Rüdiger made his international debut for [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in May 2014. He was forced to miss [[UEFA Euro 2016]] due to an injury suffered earlier in the season but he was part of the squad that won the [[2017 FIFA Confederations Cup]]. He kept his spot in the squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]], and later also took part at [[UEFA Euro 2020|Euro 2020]], the [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022 World Cup]], and [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]].

==Club career==
===VfB Stuttgart===
[[File:Antonio ruediger.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Rüdiger with [[VfB Stuttgart]] in 2012]]
On 23 July 2011, Rüdiger made his debut for [[VfB Stuttgart II]] in the [[3. Liga]] against [[Arminia Bielefeld]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/index.php?id=505718&no_cache=1&action=showSchema&lang=D&liga=bl3m&saison=11&saisonl=2011&spieltag=1&spielid=1280&cHash=03a240bdf9bb846d8dc2cc86da33d26e|title= Arminia Bielefeld&nbsp;– VfB Stuttgart II 1:2 (1:0)|publisher=German Football Association |access-date=27 January 2012|date=23 July 2011 | language = de}}</ref> Subsequently on 29 January 2012, Rüdiger made his [[Bundesliga]] debut for [[VfB Stuttgart]]'s first team in a home professional match against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]], he was replaced by [[Raphael Holzhauser]] in the 79th minute of a 3–0 defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/01/29/germany/bundesliga/vfb-stuttgart-1893-ev/borussia-monchengladbach/1122103/|title=Stuttgart vs. Borussia M'gladbach – 29 January 2012|website=Soccerway|access-date=7 November 2017}}</ref>

The following year in April 2013, Rüdiger extended his contract with Stuttgart until June 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vfb.de/en/aktuell/meldungen/news/2013/vertragsverlaengerung-antonio-ruediger-vfb-stuttgart/page/2235-1-1-.html|title=Antonio Rüdiger extends contract with VfB|date=19 April 2013 |publisher=VfB Stuttgart|access-date=19 April 2013}}</ref> On 1 June, he played in the final of the [[DFB-Pokal]] in a match lost 3–2 against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/06/01/germany/dfb-pokal/fc-bayern-munchen/vfb-stuttgart-1893-ev/1469854/|title=Bayern München vs. Stuttgart – 1 June 2013|website=Soccerway|access-date=7 November 2017}}</ref> He finished his second season in the first team with 24 appearances, plus 4 appearances and 2 goals in the reserve team.<ref name=":0" />

Rüdiger finished the 2013–14 season with 35 appearances and 2 goals.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/antonio-rudiger/192187/|title=A. Rüdiger|website=Soccerway|access-date=6 November 2017}}</ref> He finished the following season with only 20 appearances and one assist due to various injuries.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 July 2015 |title=Chelsea target Rudiger to undergo knee op |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/vfb-stuttgart/story/2523204/wolfsburg-and-chelsea-target-antonio-rudiger-has-knee-op |access-date=13 August 2022 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=25 January 2018 |title=Unlucky Rudiger has a night to forget |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/club/chelsea/363/blog/post/3359505/antonio-rudiger-ross-barkley-struggle-in-carabao-cup-defeat-to-arsenal |access-date=14 August 2022 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref>

===Roma===
On 19 August 2015, [[Serie A]] club [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] signed Rüdiger on loan from Stuttgart for €4&nbsp;million. The clubs agreed on an optional €9&nbsp;million transfer fee at the end of the one-year contract.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.asroma.it/en/news/roma_complete_rudiger_signing | title = Roma complete Rüdiger signing | date = 19 August 2015 | access-date = 19 August 2015 | publisher = A.S. Roma}}</ref>

On 12 September, he made his debut in a 2–0 away win over [[Frosinone Calcio|Frosinone]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/09/12/italy/serie-a/frosinone-calcio/as-roma/2120398/|title=Frosinone vs. Roma – 12 September 2015|website=Soccerway|access-date=6 November 2017}}</ref> On 9 January 2016 he scored his first goal for Roma in the 4th minute of a 1–1 home draw against [[A.C. Milan|Milan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/01/09/italy/serie-a/as-roma/ac-milan/2120563/|title=Roma vs. Milan – 9 January 2016|website=Soccerway|access-date=6 November 2017}}</ref> He finished his season-long loan to Roma with 37 appearances and 2 goals.<ref name=":0" /> On 30 May, Roma officially signed Rüdiger from Stuttgart for €9&nbsp;million + €0.5m bonuses on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asroma.com/it/notizie/2016/05/la-roma-ha-esercitato-il-diritto-di-opzione-per-l-acquisizione-di-antonio-rudiger|title=La Roma ha esercitato il diritto di opzione per l'acquisizione di Antonio Rudiger|date=30 May 2016|access-date=31 May 2016|publisher=A.S. Roma|language=it|archive-date=3 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220403211325/https://www.asroma.com/it/notizie/2016/05/la-roma-ha-esercitato-il-diritto-di-opzione-per-l-acquisizione-di-antonio-rudiger|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 23 February 2017, as a substitute replacing [[Kostas Manolas]] in the 46th minute of a 1–0 home defeat against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] in the round of 32 of the [[UEFA Europa League]], he was sent off with a double yellow card in the 81st minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/02/23/europe/uefa-cup/as-roma/villarreal-club-de-futbol/2380714/|title=Roma vs. Villarreal – 23 February 2017|website=Soccerway|access-date=6 November 2017}}</ref> On 30 April he was sent off with a [[Red card (soccer)|red card]] in the 93rd minute in [[Derby della Capitale]] against Lazio in a 3–1 home defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/04/30/italy/serie-a/as-roma/ss-lazio-roma/2306085/|title=Roma vs. Lazio – 30 April 2017|website=Soccerway|access-date=6 November 2017}}</ref> Rüdiger finished his second season at Roma with 35 appearances and four assists.<ref name=":0" />

===Chelsea===
[[File:Rüdiger Chelsea.jpg|thumb|upright|Rüdiger playing for [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in 2017]]
On 9 July 2017, Rüdiger joined [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] from Roma for a reported initial fee of £29&nbsp;million on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40550502|title=Antonio Rudiger: Chelsea sign Roma defender for a reported initial fee of £29m| date = 9 July 2017 | access-date = 9 July 2017 | website = BBC Sport}}</ref> He was given the number 2 shirt.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://weaintgotnohistory.sbnation.com/2017/7/9/15943710/chelsea-confirm-antonio-rudiger-shirt-number| title = Antonio Rüdiger inherits Chelsea legend's shirt number | website = sbnation.com | date = 9 July 2017 | access-date = 13 August 2017 | first = David | last = Pasztor}}</ref> He made his debut on 6 August as a substitute replacing [[Marcos Alonso (footballer, born 1990)|Marcos Alonso]] in the 79th minute in a 4–1 loss on penalties to [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[2017 FA Community Shield]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/08/06/england/community-shield/arsenal-fc/chelsea-football-club/2461684/|title=Arsenal vs. Chelsea – 6 August 2017|website=Soccerway|access-date=6 November 2017}}</ref> He made his [[Premier League]] debut six days later in a 3–2 defeat against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/08/12/england/premier-league/chelsea-football-club/burnley-fc/2462796/|title=Chelsea vs. Burnley – 12 August 2017|website=Soccerway|access-date=6 November 2017}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Chelsea in the round of 16 of the [[EFL Cup]] in a 2–1 win over [[Everton F.C.|Everton]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/10/25/england/league-cup/chelsea-football-club/everton-football-club/2594014/|title=Chelsea vs. Everton – 25 October 2017 |website=Soccerway|access-date=6 November 2017}}</ref> and his first league goal was the only one of a home win over [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] on 29 November 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/chelsea-1-swansea-0-antonio-rudiger-the-unlikely-hero-as-antonio-conte-is-sent-to-the-stands-a3705631.html|title=Chelsea 1 Swansea 0: Antonio Rudiger the unlikely hero|date=29 November 2017 |publisher=Evening Standard|access-date=29 November 2017}}</ref> On 20 October 2018, Rüdiger scored his first goal of the season, opening the scoring in a 2–2 home draw against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2018/10/20/report|title=Report: Chelsea 2 Manchester United 2|publisher=Chelsea F.C.|access-date=21 October 2018}}</ref>

On 22 December 2019, Rüdiger made a complaint about racist abuse directed against him during the away match against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], which received wide media coverage.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50797989|title=Tottenham Hotspur 0–2 Chelsea|date=22 December 2019|access-date=23 December 2019|website=BBC Sport|first=Phil|last= McNulty}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/12/22/antonio-rudiger-allegedly-racially-abused-in-tottenham-hotspur-v-chelsea-clash-11949599/ |title=Antonio Rudiger allegedly racially abused in Tottenham Hotspur v Chelsea clash |newspaper=Metro |date=22 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/11893597/chelseas-antonio-rudiger-allegedly-racially-abused-during-tottenham-game |title=Chelsea's Antonio Rudiger alleges he was racially abused by Tottenham fans |website=Sky Sports |date=23 December 2019 |access-date=23 December 2019 }}</ref> It prompted a call for government action on racism in football.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50893279 |title=Government prepared to take 'further steps' over racism in football |website=BBC Sport |date=23 December 2019 |access-date=24 December 2019 }}</ref> However, no evidence of racist abuse against Rüdiger was found after a police investigation with the police eventually dismissing the case.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/jan/06/tottenham-investigation-finds-no-evidence-of-alleged-racism-against-chelseas-rudiger |title=Investigation finds 'no evidence' of alleged racism against Chelsea's Rüdiger |newspaper=The Guardian|first=Ed |last=Aarons |date=6 January 2020 }}</ref>

[[File:2021 FIFA Club World Cup Final - 02.jpg|thumb|upright|Rüdiger (''second from bottom left'') celebrating after winning the [[2021 FIFA Club World Cup final|2021 FIFA Club World Cup]] with [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in 2021]]
On his 100th club appearance, he scored Chelsea's two goals, both headers assisted by [[Mason Mount]] in a 2–2 draw against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] at the [[King Power Stadium]] on 1 February 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/leicester-chelsea-premier-league-result-match-report-a4350981.html |title=Antonio Rudiger at the double as Chelsea rescue a point against Leicester City |newspaper=Evening Standard |first=Joe |last=Krishnans |date=2 February 2020 }}</ref> On 29 May 2021, Rüdiger won his first-ever [[UEFA Champions League]] after Chelsea beat [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] 1–0 in the [[2021 UEFA Champions League Final|final]] at the [[Estádio do Dragão]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0269-12650cedca55-37515f69768e-1000--report-chelsea-claim-second-title/ |title=Man. City 0–1 Chelsea: Havertz gives Blues second Champions League triumph |publisher=UEFA |date=29 May 2021 |access-date=29 May 2021}}</ref> On 12 April 2022, he scored his first Champions League goal in a 3–2 away win over [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in the quarter-finals of the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|2021–22]] season; however, Chelsea were eliminated from the competition by losing 5–4 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61067661 |title=Real Madrid 2–3 Chelsea |website=BBC Sport |date=12 April 2022 }}</ref> On 20 May, Rüdiger announced officially that he would leave Chelsea after five years.<ref>{{cite web |date=20 May 2022 |title=Dear Chelsea |url=https://www.theplayerstribune.com/posts/antonio-ruediger-chelsea-fc-soccer-premier-league |access-date=20 May 2022 |website=The Players' Tribune }}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
On 2 June 2022, [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] announced that Rüdiger signed as a free agent for the club, penning a four-year deal starting with the 2022–23 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Official Announcement: Rüdiger|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2022/06/02/official-announcement-rudiger|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=2 June 2022|access-date=2 June 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=2 June 2022|title=Rudiger moves to Real|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2022/06/02/rudiger-moves-to-real|publisher=Chelsea F.C.}}</ref> On 20 June 2022, Rüdiger was unveiled as a new Real Madrid player. He was given the number 22 shirt.<ref>{{cite news |title=Rüdiger unveiled as new Real Madrid player|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2022/06/20/rudiger-unveiled-as-new-real-madrid-player |date=20 June 2022 |access-date=21 June 2022 |publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref> On 10 August, he made his debut for the club, coming off the bench in a 2–0 victory over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in the [[2022 UEFA Super Cup|UEFA Super Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Real Madrid 2–0 Eintracht Frankfurt |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefasupercup/news/0278-15d6268709ab-38bef8ec34df-1000--real-madrid-win-the-super-cup/ |date=10 August 2022 |access-date=16 August 2022 |publisher=UEFA}}</ref> His first goal came on 11 September 2022, scoring the last goal in a 4–1 win over [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Real Madrid 4–1 Mallorca|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62869010|publisher=BBC|date=11 September 2022|access-date=11 September 2022}}</ref> On 11 October, he scored a header in the 95th minute against [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League group stage|Champions League group stage]], which allowed his side to draw 1–1 and qualify for the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|knockout phase]]. While jumping for the header, Rüdiger collided with Shakhtar goalkeeper [[Anatoliy Trubin]] and sustained a cut to the face that required 20 stitches.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63209183 |title=Shakhtar Donetsk 1–1 Real Madrid |website=BBC Sport |date=11 October 2022 |accessdate=11 October 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=12 October 2022 |title=Antonio Rudiger split his head open for Madrid, needs 20 stitches |url=https://www.sport.es/en/news/real-madrid/antonio-rudiger-split-his-head-open-for-madrid-needs-20-stitches-77145530 |work=[[Sport.es]] |accessdate=12 October 2022}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 Real Madrid CF season|2023–24 season]], he achieved his first La Liga and second Champions League title,<ref>{{cite web |last=Corrigan |first=Dermot |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5532580/2024/06/01/real-madrid-champions-league-winners-perez-ancelotti-bellingham-vinicius-jr/ |title=Real Madrid are Champions League winners again – and their power only looks set to grow |work=The New York Times |date=1 June 2024 }}</ref> in which he was named in the Team of the Season for the latter.<ref name="auto"/> On 1 April 2025, he scored the decisive goal against [[Real Sociedad]] during extra time, securing his team's place in the [[2025 Copa del Rey final|Copa del Rey final]] with a 5–4 aggregate victory.<ref>{{cite web |last=Coates |first=Charlotte |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cg5d582nl4gt |title=Real Madrid 4–4 Real Sociedad |publisher=BBC Sport |date=1 April 2025 }}</ref> On 27 April during the 2–3 Copa del Rey final defeat to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], Rüdiger received a red card on the bench after continuously attempting to threaten a referee after a controversial challenge including throwing an object, and he was continuously held back by his teammates. Rüdiger's actions were heavily condemned, and he was ultimately handed a six-match ban.<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Corrigan |first1=Dermot |last2=Millar |first2=Colin |date=27 April 2025 |title=Real Madrid's red cards: Antonio Rudiger 'threw object' at referee, Jude Bellingham's 'aggressive behaviour' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6314786/2025/04/27/real-madrid-red-cards-copa-rudiger-bellingham-vazquez/ |access-date=28 April 2025 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=27 April 2025 |title=Rüdiger apologises to referee over Copa red |url=https://www.espn.com/football/story/_/id/44881559/real-madrid-antonio-rudiger-issues-apology-copa-del-rey-final-red-card |access-date=28 April 2025 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=27 April 2025 |title=Antonio Rudiger facing huge ban after throwing MISSILE at referee from touchline in complete head-loss at end of Real Madrid's Copa del Rey final defeat to Barcelona | url = https://www.goal.com/en/lists/antonio-rudiger-huge-ban-real-madrid-s-copa-del-rey-final-barcelona/bltb975e4afde5320fd | access-date = 28 April 2025 | website = goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/ckge9rp8379o | title = Rudiger given six-game ban for throwing object at referee | website = BBC Sport | date = 29 April 2025 | access-date = 13 May 2025 | first = Emma | last = Smith}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:20180602 FIFA Friendly Match Austria vs. Germany Team Germany 850 0740.jpg|thumb|Rüdiger lined up for [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in 2018]]
Rüdiger was eligible to play for Germany and [[Sierra Leone national football team|Sierra Leone]], his mother's homeland<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.footballsierraleone.net/as-roma-sign-antonio-ruediger-on-loan/ |title= AS Roma sign Antonio Ruediger on loan |access-date= 1 April 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416073732/http://www.footballsierraleone.net/as-roma-sign-antonio-ruediger-on-loan/ |archive-date= 16 April 2016}}</ref> and was a member of several German national youth football teams up to the [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]] team.<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 May 2024 |title=Antonio Rüdiger: Real Madrid's UEFA Champions League-winning defender, made in the Bundesliga |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/antonio-rudiger-real-madrid-chelsea-defender-made-in-dortmund-stuttgart-16097 |access-date=23 June 2024 |website=bundesliga.com – the official Bundesliga website |language=en}}</ref>

He made his debut for the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]] on 13 May 2014 in a 0–0 draw against [[Poland national football team|Poland]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/match/131992/germany-vs-poland/report | title=Germany 0–0 Poland |website=Goal.com | access-date=14 May 2014}}</ref> Although he was initially included in his nation's 23-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2016]], Rüdiger was later ruled out of the tournament due to injury, after tearing the [[anterior cruciate ligament]] in his right knee during a training session on 7 June.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/germany/story/2888155/antonio-rudiger-tears-acl-in-germany-training-for-euro-2016|title=Antonio Rudiger tears ACL in Germany training, ruled out of Euro 2016|website=ESPN FC|date=7 June 2016|access-date=8 June 2016}}</ref>
Rüdiger was part of the Germany national squad which won the [[2017 FIFA Confederations Cup]] in Russia. He played four matches in the tournament, including the 1–0 win over [[Chile national football team|Chile]] in the [[2017 FIFA Confederations Cup|final]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Johnston|first1=Neil|title=Chile 0–1 Germany|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40464139|access-date=11 January 2018|website=BBC Sport|date=2 July 2017}}</ref> On 8 October 2017, he headed his first international goal in a 5–1 home win over [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|World Cup qualifying]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Germany 5–1 Azerbaijan|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41533920|access-date=11 January 2018|website=BBC Sport|date=8 October 2017}}</ref>
[[File:2022 FIFA World Cup Germany 1–2 Japan - (19).jpg|left|thumb|299x299px|Rüdiger playing for [[Germany national football team|Germany]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]
Rüdiger was included in Germany's final 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] on 4 June 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dw.com/en/germany-announce-final-world-cup-squad-with-manuel-neuer-without-leroy-san%C3%A9/a-44064011|title=Germany announce final World Cup squad, with Manuel Neuer, without Leroy Sané|publisher=Deutsche Welle|access-date=4 June 2018}}</ref> On 23 June, he was picked up for the second group stage match against [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] as first choice [[centre-back]] [[Mats Hummels]] suffered an injury, the game ended 2–1 win for Germany.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/world-cup-2018-germany-sweden-mats-hummels-a8414891.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220507/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/world-cup-2018-germany-sweden-mats-hummels-a8414891.html |archive-date=7 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|title=World Cup 2018: Mats Hummels says Germany's dramatic win over Sweden could be their turning point|newspaper=The Independent|date=24 June 2018 |access-date=1 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jun/23/toni-kroos-germany-sweden-world-cup-match-report|title=Toni Kroos brings off late miracle for Germany to stun Sweden|newspaper=The Guardian|date=23 June 2018 |access-date=1 August 2018}}</ref> Four days later, he did not play the last group stage match and his side were knocked out by [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] after a 2–0 defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2018/jun/27/world-cup-2018-south-korea-v-germany-live|title=South Korea 2–0 Germany: World Cup 2018 – as it happened|newspaper=The Guardian|date=27 June 2018 |access-date=1 August 2018}}</ref> On 19 May 2021, Rüdiger was selected to the squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/em-kader-offiziell-loew-beruft-mueller-hummels-und-volland-804642/artikel|title=EM-Kader offiziell: Löw beruft Müller, Hummels und Volland|date=19 May 2021|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|access-date=19 May 2021}}</ref> He played every minute in the tournament for Germany as they were eliminated by [[England national football team|England]] in the [[UEFA Euro 2020 knockout phase#England vs Germany|round of 16]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/teams/players/250028211--antonio-rudiger/|title=Antonio Rüdiger – UEFA Euro 2020|website=[[UEFA]]|publisher=Union of European Football Associations|access-date=20 September 2021}}{{dead link|date=March 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

In November 2022, Rüdiger was called up for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite web|last=Steinberg|first=Jacob|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/nov/20/antonio-rudiger-never-count-germany-out-anything-can-happen-world-cup-qatar-2022|title=Antonio Rüdiger: 'Never count Germany out – anything can happen'|work=The Guardian|date=20 November 2022}}</ref> However, Germany were knocked out from the group stage, as they finished third behind [[Japan national football team|Japan]] and [[Spain national football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2022/12/01/world-cup-exists-belgium-and-germany-knocked-out-in-group-stages-while-japan-top-group-e|title=World Cup exits: Belgium and Germany knocked out in group stages while Japan top Group E|publisher=Euronews|date=2 December 2022}}</ref>

Rüdiger was included in the Germany squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 May 2024 |title=Diese Spieler hat der DFB bereits für die EM nominiert |url=https://www.kicker.de/diese-spieler-hat-der-dfb-bereits-fuer-die-em-nominiert-1024611/artikel |access-date=15 May 2024 |publisher=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref>

On 21 May 2026, he was selected in Germany’s 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/news/bundestrainer-nagelsmann-gibt-wm-kader-bekannt|title=Bundestrainer Nagelsmann gibt WM-Kader bekannt|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|language=de|date=21 May 2026|access-date=21 May 2026}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Normally a centre-back, Rüdiger is a versatile defender, who is also capable of playing as a [[Full-back (association football)|full-back]] on either flank.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.calciomercato.com/news/rudiger-dall-inter-ai-milioni-di-conte-la-roma-blinda-il-leader--57489 |title=Rudiger, dall'Inter ai milioni di Conte: la Roma blinda il leader della difesa 2.0 |publisher=www.calciomercato.com |language=it |date=10 February 2017 |access-date=21 October 2018 }}</ref> In 2015, ''[[ESPN]]'' described him as a "tall, quick and athletic defender who is ... comfortable with the ball at his feet", also touting him as an "interesting prospect" who "has all the necessary physical attributes to become a top-level centre-back".<ref name="Rising star">{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/blog/the-scouts-notebook/78/post/2514270/stuttgart-and-germany-defender-antonio-rudiger-profile |title=Rising star Antonio Rudiger would be best served by Bundesliga stay |publisher=ESPN |last1=Dorrington |first1=Nick |date=7 July 2015 |access-date=20 October 2018 }}</ref> His Chelsea profile described him as a "tough tackler" and a "commanding presence in the air".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/teams/first-team/antonio-ruediger?pageTab=biography |title=Antonio Rudiger |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |access-date=5 October 2018}}</ref> In addition to his strong physical attributes and aggressive playing style, he is also known for his leadership qualities and passing ability.<ref name="Rising star"/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2021/05/27/making-antonio-rudiger-chelsea-hard-man-lives-eat-eaten-ethos/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220112/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2021/05/27/making-antonio-rudiger-chelsea-hard-man-lives-eat-eaten-ethos/ |archive-date=12 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=The making of Antonio Rudiger: How Chelsea hard man lives by 'eat or be eaten' ethos |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |last1=Dean |first1=Sam |date=27 May 2021 |access-date=28 May 2021 }}{{cbignore}}</ref> Rüdiger’s speed and athleticism, coupled with his understanding of the game, allow him to excel both in man-to-man situations and in zonal marking.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://onefootball.com/en/news/real-madrid-defender-confident-about-second-leg-tie-against-not-dangerous-man-city-37438465 |title= Real Madrid defender confident about second leg tie against 'not dangerous' Man City |website=OneFootball|access-date=10 May 2023}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Rüdiger was born in [[Berlin]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe230406/antonio-ruediger/ |title=Antonio Rüdiger: Profile |website=worldfootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |access-date=28 June 2020}}</ref> to an [[Afro-German]] father, Matthias, and a Sierra Leonean mother, Lily. He was named after Spanish actor [[Antonio Banderas]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rüdiger |first1=Antonio |title=AAntonio Rüdiger: "Me pusieron mi nombre por Antonio Banderas" |date=10 August 2023 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jY-qkmG8rs4 |publisher=[[YouTube]] |access-date=1 September 2024}}</ref> He grew up in the Berlin neighbourhood of [[Neukölln (locality)|Neukölln]] and is the half-brother of [[Sahr Senesie]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rüdiger |first1=Antonio |title=Antonio Rudiger: This is the story of my life |date=20 July 2016 |url=https://medium.com/forza-roma/antonio-rudiger-this-is-the-story-of-my-life-a733366bfab3 |publisher=[[Medium.com]] |access-date=15 December 2022}}</ref><ref name="DFB">{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/antonio-ruediger-manchmal-musst-du-volles-risiko-gehen-31460/|title=Antonio Rüdiger: "Manchmal musst du volles Risiko gehen"|publisher=German Football Association |access-date=21 October 2012|date=24 February 2012|language=de}}</ref> Rüdiger has often spoken out on [[Racism in association football|racism in the sport]], most notably after a match against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] on 24 February 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://talksport.com/football/673771/racism-won-rudiger-tottenham-chelsea-abuse/ |title=IT'S SAD 'Racism won' says Antonio Rudiger after Tottenham fans jeer Chelsea defender in wake of abuse claims|website=talkSport.com |date=24 February 2020 |access-date=16 September 2020}}</ref> In 2021, he wrote an article for ''[[The Players' Tribune]]'', entitled "This Article Will Not Solve Racism in Football", on the subject, discussing his experiences with racism throughout his life and career, and potential ways to fight it.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theplayerstribune.com/posts/antonio-ruediger-champions-league-soccer-racism-chelsea |title=This Article Will Not Solve Racism in Football |publisher=The Players' Tribune |last1=Rüdiger |first1=Antonio |date=27 May 2021 |access-date=28 May 2021 }}</ref> He is married to  Laura Rüdiger<ref>{{cite web | url = https://thesportsgrail.com/who-is-laura-rudiger-wife-of-antonio-rudiger-bio-age-family-children-religion-and-instagram/ | title = Who is Laura Rudiger wife of Antonio Rudiger, bio, age, family, children, religion and Instagram | website = thesportsgrail.com | date = 22 February 2024 | access-date = 5 April 2024 | first = Rizu | last = Shulka}}</ref> and he has a son and a daughter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/antonio-ruediger-no-one-knows-what-will-happen-at-chelsea-i-couldnt-wait-until-june-to-sort-out-my-future-fjr2k8j75|last=The Times|title=No one knows what will happen at Chelsea – I couldn't wait until June to sort out my future|location=London|date=20 May 2022|accessdate=21 September 2022}}</ref>

Rüdiger is a practising [[Muslim]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/champions-league-final-antonio-r%C3%BCdiger-a-quiet-leader-for-chelsea-and-germany/a-57697527|title=Champions League final: Antonio Rüdiger, a quiet leader for Chelsea and Germany|publisher=Deutsche Welle|access-date=20 August 2021}}</ref> In 2020, Rüdiger gave a [[Like button|like]] to an Islamistic diatribe against French President [[Emmanuel Macron]] on [[Instagram]]. He later issued an apology for not reading the full post which was written in cyrillic.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Antonio Rüdiger entschuldigt sich nach Like für Islamismus-Post von Khabib Nurmagomedov |date=6 November 2020 |url=https://www.sport1.de/news/fussball/dfb-team/2020/11/antonio-ruediger |language=de}}</ref> In March 2024, Rüdiger posted a photo of himself in a white [[Ihram clothing|ihram robe]] and on a prayer rug, with his index finger of his right hand pointing to the sky, with a greeting for [[Ramadan]] in the caption.

Former editor-in-chief of the  [[Bild|''Bild Zeitung'']], a German tabloid, [[Julian Reichelt]] commented on the athlete's [[Tawhid|tauhīd]] gesture claiming it was called the 'IS finger' by the [[Federal Office for the Protection of the Constitution|Office for the Protection of Constitution]] and regarding as a sign of [[Islamism]]. In response to this, the player agreed to an interview,<ref name="bild.de">{{Cite web |date=26 March 2024 |title=DFB und Antonio Rüdiger erstatten Anzeige: Wegen dieser religiöse Geste |url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/fussball/antonio-ruediger-anzeigen-von-ihm-und-dfb-es-geht-um-diese-religioese-geste-87651322.bild.html |access-date=6 January 2025 |website=bild.de |language=de}}</ref> with the same tabloid, saying: 
<blockquote>As a devout Muslim, I practice my faith, but I firmly distance myself from any kind of extremism and accusations of Islamism. Violence and terrorism are absolutely unacceptable. I stand for peace and tolerance. </blockquote> The [[Federal Ministry of the Interior (Germany)|German Ministry of Interior]] also made a clarifying statement regarding Reichelt's claim saying:<blockquote>From the point of view of the BMI, the so-called 'tauhid' finger is to be understood as a declaration of faith and, in this respect, classified as unproblematic with regard to public safety. This applies regardless of the fact that Islamist groups appropriate this symbol and misuse it for their own purposes.</blockquote> As a result, together with the [[German Football Association]], Rüdiger filed a complaint against Reichelt for defamation, insult, and incitement to hatred. The proceedings were later terminated by the [[Public Prosecutor General (Germany)|Office of the Public Prosecutor]] based on grounds that the statement was covered under freedom of expression.<ref name="bild.de"/><ref>{{Cite journal |date=26 March 2024 |title=Antonio Rüdiger und DFB stellen Strafanzeige gegen Julian Reichelt |url=https://www.spiegel.de/sport/fussball/antonio-ruediger-und-dfb-stellen-strafanzeige-gegen-julian-reichelt-a-f82fbf01-0890-4d4b-8e4a-481536a4abb9 |journal=Der Spiegel |language=de |issn=2195-1349 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240326110104/https://www.spiegel.de/sport/fussball/antonio-ruediger-und-dfb-stellen-strafanzeige-gegen-julian-reichelt-a-f82fbf01-0890-4d4b-8e4a-481536a4abb9 |archive-date=26 March 2024}}</ref>

